// for tutorial/showcase bird-in-hand Tutorial bird-in-hand Hints
First, add people using the Add People button. Provide some info for each person by hitting Capture Insights.
Finally, discover where you should focus with the See Results button. When this tutorial is over, it will be toggled off. Use the options menu to turn it back on. Add people using the New button here. A screen will be presented allowing you to enter basic info for that person. You can go through questions for each one at a time - just click the check box icon on this screen, or return to the main menu and use the Capture Insights button to go through them all. Answer simple questions about each person here. Just select a name and a series of questions will be presented. The icon on the right indicates your progress. A check mark means you\'re done with that person. Just hit Done to return to the main screen when you\'re done. Respond to questions here. Use the slider to provide a response from 1 to 10. Try to answer each question independently of the others (not what you think the final rating should be). Hit the Next Question button to move to the next question. After each person is evaluated, they will be represented on this report. The ones in the upper right quadrant are the ones where you should focus your time. Use the Summary button to see a summary of the results.
